<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>



<head>



<title>CREATE-LEFT-TURN-BUTTON</title>

</head>
<body>

	<h3><i>This micro-behaviour is an example<u> </u>for creating a button.</i> 
	</h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>CREATE-LEFT-TURN-BUTTON</b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>substitute-text-area-for upper-left-corner-x 5   
substitute-text-area-for upper-left-corner-y 225  
substitute-text-area-for lower-right-corner-x 107   
substitute-text-area-for lower-right-corner-y 255  
substitute-text-area-for button-label LEFT  
substitute-text-area-for number-of-degrees 10  
substitute-text-area-for keyboard-shortcut L
create-button 
  "upper-left-corner-x" "upper-left-corner-y"&nbsp;; upper left corner (from the upper left corner of the applet) 
  "lower-right-corner-x" "lower-right-corner-y"&nbsp;; lower right corner
  "button-label"&nbsp;; label
  "turn-left number-of-degrees"&nbsp;; action
  "keyboard-shortcut"&nbsp;; keyboard shortcut</pre>
	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>All the parameters can be changed. If you don't want a keyboard shortcut 
	then remove the last line of code.</p>

	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>


	<p>

	<a title="CREATE-RIGHT-TURN-BUTTON" href="CREATE-RIGHT-TURN-BUTTON.html">

	CREATE-RIGHT-TURN-BUTTON</a> is a variant of this for turning right.</p>

	<p>

	<a href="CREATE-SWITCH.html">CREATE-SWITCH</a> creates a switch that can be 
	either on or off.</p>
	<p>

	<a title="CREATE-PLOT" href="CREATE-PLOT.html">

	CREATE-PLOT</a> and

	<a title="CREATE-SLIDER" href="CREATE-SLIDER.html">

	CREATE-SLIDER</a> also create an interface element.</p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>This creates a NetLogo button. The last parameter, <i>the action</i>, is 

	available to micro-behaviours such as

	<a title="DO-BUTTON-COMMAND" href="DO-BUTTON-COMMAND.html">

	DO-BUTTON-COMMAND</a> as the value of the <i>button-command</i> variable.

	</p>

	<h2>History</h2>
	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn.
</body>
</html>

